IS  - 1
KW  - heterogeneous agents
KW  - imperfect information
KW  - monetary policy
KW  - New Keynesian
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0020-6598
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/iere.70007
Y2  - 2026/04/24
N2  - ABSTRACT Monetary policy transmission in the benchmark New Keynesian (NK) model hinges on the Full Information Rational Expectations (FIRE) assumption, especially via indirect general equilibrium (GE) effects. This paper relaxes FIRE by introducing noisy information into a Heterogeneous-Agent NK model with financial frictions. Noisy information dampens amplification by muting GE effects, aligning model dynamics with empirical evidence, and resolving the forward guidance puzzle. It also broadens the determinacy region for policy rules. Finally, I explore belief shocks, showing that transitory ?animal spirits? can have persistent effects, offering new insights into the macroeconomic consequences of information frictions.
ER  - 

