KW  - Knightian uncertainty
KW  - strict dominance
KW  - subjective expected utility
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0020-6598
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/iere.70015
Y2  - 2026/04/24
N2  - ABSTRACT A wide variety of financial instruments allows risk-averse traders to reduce their exposure to risk. This raises the question of what financial instruments allow ambiguity-averse traders to reduce their exposure to ambiguity. We show in this paper that price-contingent orders, such as limit orders, are sufficient: In a two-period trading model, an ambiguity-averse trader who trades with limit orders is observationally indistinguishable from an ambiguity-neutral trader with the same risk preferences.
ER  - 

